            . I am a <rs id="t18190421-246-viclabel1374" type="occupation">tailor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190421-246-victim2286 t18190421-246-viclabel1374"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18190421-246-crimeloc1375">James-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18190421-246-crimeloc1375" type="placeName" value="James-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18190421-246-crimeloc1375" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190421-246-off1372 t18190421-246-crimeloc1375"></join>. On the 14th of March, about four o'clock, I went out with my wife - I returned about five, found my parlour window open, and the canary bird taken away, with two spoons, and 12 s. in copper. I saw the prisoner in the passage calling to the lodgers - he was apprehended next morning. I found my spoons at a silversmith's in Cheapside - I knew the prisoner before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190421-246-person2288">
                  THOMAS 
                  THOMPSON
               <interp inst="t18190421-246-person2288" type="surname" value="THOMPSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-246-person2288" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-246-person2288" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I apprehended the prisoner at a public-house on Saffron-hill. I told him I took him for stealing the spoons - he said he sold them in Cheapside, and told me where to find the bird.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190421-246-person2289">
